<br>
The fact of the matter is that I hate SUVs for the exact same reasons as you and several other posters here hate Hondas:  <br>
<br>
Personal prejudice.<br>
<br>
It really doesn't matter.  What it amounts to in my area anyway is observed socioeconomic trends amplified somewhat by personal prejudice.  If you wanted to get all psychoanalytic on me, you could probably surmise that I secretly lust over the Lincoln Navigator simply because I couldn't afford to own one.  So I make up some @#%$ about soccer moms to quiet the pain of envy that I feel in my soul.  Or you could say that I hate Lincoln Navigators because they really do look like lardass heaps of @#%$ in a more absolute and universal sense. Makes no real difference in the long run because nobody is gonna prove me wrong <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    You may sway public opinion on the issue...but chances are good you wont sway mine.  I figure that people *should* drive SUVs for one reason:  Utility.  i.e. you're the type of person who has to haul lots of @#%$/people around all the time.  I could go off on a tangential rant about excessive lifestyles in modern America, overpopulation, and shortages of available resources, but I already know what you'd say about that--and I figure time and Darwinian selection will eventually take care of the problem.  Ibid personal prejudice.<br>
<br>
I figure the reason people don't drive station wagons much any more is because the world finally realized they are pretty stupid looking.  Hopefully the same thing will happen with the SUV.  Motor Trend used to rave about the Taurus wagon for awhile...but wow that thing looks like a turd on wheels to me.<br>
<br>
I like my Honda for several reasons:  its cheap, its fuel efficient, it gets me where I want to go (quickly and expeditiously I might add), and its not too dumb looking.  Granted if I were some rice-shitter that gimped it out with spoilers, hydraulics, window tinting and Rockford Fosgate stickers it might become dumb looking...but alas I am not said rice-shitter.  <br>
<br>
Personally I'd rather be driving a hemi 'Cuda in a barren unpopulated world like something out of Stephen King's &quot;The Stand&quot; or &quot;The Road Warrior&quot;...where soccer moms are of minimal concern and I could just reduce their vehicles to rubble with a hood-mounted rocket launcher...but such fantasies are unrealistic and somewhat sociopathic.<br>
<br>
btw...plz define &quot;peddle car.&quot;  You lost me a bit on that one.  <br>
<br>
<br>
